  <div class="page-title">Privacy Policy</div>
  <div class="updated">Last updated: June 2026</div>

  <p>At Expence Tracker, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our expense tracking application.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect only the minimum information necessary to provide our service:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Your name and email address when you register.</li>
    <li><strong>Expense Data:</strong> Expense names, amounts, categories, and dates that you enter.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Basic app usage data to improve our service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To provide and maintain the expense tracking service.</li>
    <li>To sync your data securely across devices.</li>
    <li>To improve the app experience based on usage patterns.</li>
    <li>To send important service-related notifications.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
  <p>Your data is stored securely using Google Firebase — an industry-leading cloud platform with enterprise-grade security. All data is encrypted in transit and at rest. We use Firebase Authentication for secure login management.</p>

  <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We do not share your financial data with anyone. Your expense data is private and accessible only to you.</p>

  <h2>5. Cookies & Local Storage</h2>
  <p>We use browser local storage to cache your expense data for faster loading and offline access. This data stays on your device and is never transmitted to any third party.</p>

  <h2>6. Google AdSense</h2>
  <p>We may display advertisements served by Google AdSense. Google may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to our website or other websites. You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" style="color:#C9A84C">Google Ads Settings</a>.</p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Access and download your personal data at any time.</li>
    <li>Delete your account and all associated data.</li>
    <li>Opt out of non-essential data collection.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Expence Tracker is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

  <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page with an updated date.</p>

  <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at our <a href="/Expense_Tracker/contact.html" style="color:#C9A84C">Contact page</a>.</p>
